score-abc2lynotexecutable:
{{doc-important|Do not translate "$wgScoreAbc2Ly" argument.}}
Displayed if the ABC to LilyPond converter could not be executed. $1 is the path to the abc2ly binary.
score-abcconversionerr: Displayed if the ABC to LilyPond conversion failed. $1 is the error (generally big block of text in a pre tag)
score-audioconversionerr: Displayed if the MIDI to MP3 conversion failed. $1 is the error (generally big block of text in a pre tag)
score-audiooverridenotfound:
{{doc-important|Do not translate "override_audio" argument.}}
Displayed if the file specified with the override_audio="…" attribute could not be found. $1 is the value of the override_ogg attribute.
score-audio-alt: Text shown instead of an audio player if the user's browser does not support audio. This may also appear in search engine excerpts and the like. $1 is a download link with link text given by {{msg-mw|score-audio-alt-link}}.
score-audio-alt-link: The link text used for the link embedded within the {{msg-mw|score-audio-alt}} message.
score-backend-error:
Parameters:
* $1 - result message which was returned
score-compilererr: Displayed if the LilyPond code could not be compiled. $1 is the error (generally big block of text in a pre tag)
score-convertoverrideaudio:
{{doc-important|Do not translate "override_audio" argument.}}
Displayed if both sound="1" and override_audio="…" were specified.
score-deprecated-category:
{{tracking category name}}
Name of [[mw:Help:Tracking categories|tracking category]] to list pages which override either the midi or audio file.
score-deprecated-category-desc: Description on [[Special:TrackingCategories]] for the {{msg-mw|score-deprecated-category}} tracking category.
score-download-midi-file: Content of link to download MIDI file of score shown in score popup
score-download-source-file: Content of link to download the LilyPond  file of score shown in score popup
score-error-category: {{tracking category name}} Name of [[mw:Help:Tracking categories|tracking category]] to list pages where there was an error rendering the tag.
score-error-category-desc: Description on [[Special:TrackingCategories]] for the {{msg-mw|score-error-category}} tracking category.
score-exec-disabled: Message shown in the page when rendering of new score files is disabled
score-file-list-error: Displayed if the extension cannot read from a directory.
score-fallbacknotexecutable:
{{doc-important|Do not translate "$wgScoreFluidsynth".}}
Displayed if FluidSynth. $1 is the path to the FluidSynth binary.
score-gs-error: Displayed if there is an error when running Ghostscript.
score-invalidaudiooverride: Displayed if the file specified with the override_audio="…" attribute is invalid. $1 is the value of the override_audio attribute.
score-invalidlang: Displayed if the lang="…" attribute contains an unrecognized score language. $1 is the unrecognized language.
score-invalidnotelanguage: Displayed if the note-language="…" attribute contains an unrecognized note language. $1 is the unrecognized note language. $2 is comma separated list of available languages.
score-lamenotexecutable: Displayed if LAME could not be executed. $1 is the path to the LAME binary.
score-midioverridenotfound: Displayed if the file specified with the override_midi="…" attribute could not be found. $1 is the value of the override_midi attribute.
score-noimages: Displayed if no score images were rendered.
score-nomidi: Displayed if MIDI file generation was requested but no MIDI file was generated.
score-nooutput: Displayed if an output directory could not be created. $1 is the name of the directory.
score-nops: Displayed if LilyPond fails to create the expected PostScript file.
score-notelanguagewithraw: Displayed if the "note-language" attribute is used for scores in raw mode
score-notexecutable: Displayed if LilyPond binary cannot be executed. $1 is the path to the LilyPond binary.
score-pregreplaceerr: Displayed if a PCRE regular expression replacement failed.
score-readerr: Displayed if the extension could not read a file. $1 is the path to the file that could not be read.
score-scripterr: Displayed when a script fails to run for unspecified reasons.
score-soundfontnotexists: Displayed if soundfont could not be found. $1 is the path to the soundfont file.
score-trimerr: Displayed if the extension failed to trim an output image. $1 is the error (generally big block of text in a pre tag)
score-versionerr: Displayed if the extension failed to obtain the version string of LilyPond. $1 is the LilyPond stdout output generated by the attempt.
